<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <!--
      NEEDED: our externalBin sidecar (the compiled @openfusion/engine binary)
      loads better-sqlite3's native .node addon at runtime. Hardened runtime
      enforces same-Team-ID library validation by default, which blocks
      dlopen()-ing that addon (ERR_DLOPEN_FAILED) unless this is disabled.
      Verified against docs/research/2026-07-04-m7-tauri-verification.md.
    -->
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation</key>
    <true/>

    <!--
      LEFT COMMENTED, but EXPECT TO LIKELY NEED THESE: the bundle's second
      executable, `Contents/MacOS/openfusion-engine` (a `@yao-pkg/pkg`-
      compiled Node binary), embeds and JITs V8 IN-PROCESS -- exactly the
      Electron-like case every Tauri signing guide pairs with
      disable-library-validation. Node's own official release binaries ship
      both entitlements for this reason; a hardened-runtime V8 process
      without them typically aborts at startup. The WKWebView (what Tauri
      itself uses on macOS) runs JS inside Apple's own entitled, sandboxed
      helper process, so IT likely doesn't need these -- the sidecar is the
      probable consumer. Per the research doc: verify empirically -- build a
      signed release WITHOUT them first, then check BOTH that the app window
      launches AND that the engine sidecar actually starts (cockpit screens
      work; `ps aux | grep openfusion-engine` shows it running) -- only if
      the app crashes on launch OR the sidecar fails to start, uncomment
      this block and rebuild (a full rebuild, not just a re-sign: the
      bundler applies this same entitlements plist to every binary it
      signs, including the sidecar). See apps/desktop/BUILDING.md's JIT
      empirical check section.

    <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-jit</key>
    <true/>
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-unsigned-executable-memory</key>
    <true/>
    -->
</dict>
</plist>
